  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 3507d679efa283143b52308c9a6a3292, type: 3}
  m_Name: GSWTIAH_Module_1_Q7
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::QuestionData
  question: 'Why is it important to create an integrated security domain system?

    [Select
    Two]'
  answers:
  - "Until recently, organizations have responded to security concerns by deploying
    a new tool to address each new risk. We\u2019ve observed one company was using
    85 tools from 45 different software vendors! Now they have to install, configure,
    manage, patch, upgrade, and pay for dozens of non-integrated solutions with limited
    views of the landscape. "
  - "Costly and complex fragmented security capabilities provide the visibility and
    coordination needed to stop today\u2019s sophisticated attacks."
  - The security portfolio structured around domains presents a less organized fashion
    to make sense of threats using logs, data, threats, flows, packets, etc.
  - Because it involves the partner ecosystem that allows collaboration across companies
    and competitors, to understand global threats and data, and adapt to new threats.
  - Because the traditional defense strategy is not to layer on another point-product
    tool or technology to an already fragmented and disjointed IT environment.
  maxSelections: 1
  correctAnswerIndices: 0000000003000000
  correctMessage: You're doing great!
  incorrectMessage: Almost had it!
